                    <span>If you're a musician, you will understand that the tune "Giant Steps" is really challenging, the complex chords progression and how to play improvitation along with that chords progression.
<br />
<br />I remember when I read Guitar Magazine, Mahavishnu John McLaughlin said that if you want to hear something fast than you should hear John Coltrane's playing.
<br />
<br />You can hear the romantic side of John Coltrane on "Naima", he wrote this song for his wife.
<br />
<br />If you never heard John Coltrane before then this is the most recommended and most essential album from him.</span>
                  
